 502:../Core/FreeRTOS-Kernel/tasks.c **** /* Context switches are held pending while the scheduler is suspended.  Also,
 503:../Core/FreeRTOS-Kernel/tasks.c ****  * interrupts must not manipulate the xStateListItem of a TCB, or any of the
 504:../Core/FreeRTOS-Kernel/tasks.c ****  * lists the xStateListItem can be referenced from, if the scheduler is suspended.
 505:../Core/FreeRTOS-Kernel/tasks.c ****  * If an interrupt needs to unblock a task while the scheduler is suspended then it
 506:../Core/FreeRTOS-Kernel/tasks.c ****  * moves the task's event list item into the xPendingReadyList, ready for the
 507:../Core/FreeRTOS-Kernel/tasks.c ****  * kernel to move the task from the pending ready list into the real ready list
 508:../Core/FreeRTOS-Kernel/tasks.c ****  * when the scheduler is unsuspended.  The pending ready list itself can only be
 509:../Core/FreeRTOS-Kernel/tasks.c ****  * accessed from a critical section.
 510:../Core/FreeRTOS-Kernel/tasks.c ****  *
 511:../Core/FreeRTOS-Kernel/tasks.c ****  * Updates to uxSchedulerSuspended must be protected by both the task lock and the ISR lock
